{
  "chapter": {
    "id": "dra:proverbs.20",
    "translationId": "dra",
    "bookSlug": "proverbs",
    "chapterNumber": 20,
    "referenceLabel": "Proverbs 20",
    "summary": "Source text for Proverbs 20 in Douay-Rheims Bible (Challoner)."
  },
  "verses": [
    {
      "id": "dra:proverbs.20.1",
      "translationId": "dra",
      "bookSlug": "proverbs",
      "chapterNumber": 20,
      "verseNumber": 1,
      "referenceLabel": "Proverbs 20:1",
      "text": "Wine is a luxurious thing, and drunkenness riotous: whosoever is delighted therewith, shall not be wise.",
      "paragraphStart": true
    },
    {
      "id": "dra:proverbs.20.2",
      "translationId": "dra",
      "bookSlug": "proverbs",
      "chapterNumber": 20,
      "verseNumber": 2,
      "referenceLabel": "Proverbs 20:2",
      "text": "As the roaring of a lion, so also is the dread of a king: he that provoketh him, sinneth against his own soul.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "dra:proverbs.20.3",
      "translationId": "dra",
      "bookSlug": "proverbs",
      "chapterNumber": 20,
      "verseNumber": 3,
      "referenceLabel": "Proverbs 20:3",
      "text": "It is an honour for a man to separate himself from quarrels: but all fools are meddling with reproaches.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "dra:proverbs.20.4",
      "translationId": "dra",
      "bookSlug": "proverbs",
      "chapterNumber": 20,
      "verseNumber": 4,
      "referenceLabel": "Proverbs 20:4",
      "text": "Because of the cold the sluggard would not plough: he shall beg therefore in the summer, and it shall not be given him.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "dra:proverbs.20.5",
      "translationId": "dra",
      "bookSlug": "proverbs",
      "chapterNumber": 20,
      "verseNumber": 5,
      "referenceLabel": "Proverbs 20:5",
      "text": "Counsel in the heart of a man is like deep water: but a wise man will draw it out.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "dra:proverbs.20.6",
      "translationId": "dra",
      "bookSlug": "proverbs",
      "chapterNumber": 20,
      "verseNumber": 6,
      "referenceLabel": "Proverbs 20:6",
      "text": "Many men are called merciful: but who shall find a faithful man?",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "dra:proverbs.20.7",
      "translationId": "dra",
      "bookSlug": "proverbs",
      "chapterNumber": 20,
      "verseNumber": 7,
      "referenceLabel": "Proverbs 20:7",
      "text": "The just that walketh in his simplicity, shall leave behind him blessed children.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "dra:proverbs.20.8",
      "translationId": "dra",
      "bookSlug": "proverbs",
      "chapterNumber": 20,
      "verseNumber": 8,
      "referenceLabel": "Proverbs 20:8",
      "text": "The king, that sitteth on the throne of judgment, scattereth away all evil with his look.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "dra:proverbs.20.9",
      "translationId": "dra",
      "bookSlug": "proverbs",
      "chapterNumber": 20,
      "verseNumber": 9,
      "referenceLabel": "Proverbs 20:9",
      "text": "Who can say: My heart is clean, I am pure from sin?",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "dra:proverbs.20.10",
      "translationId": "dra",
      "bookSlug": "proverbs",
      "chapterNumber": 20,
      "verseNumber": 10,
      "referenceLabel": "Proverbs 20:10",
      "text": "Diverse weights and diverse measures, both are abominable before God.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "dra:proverbs.20.11",
      "translationId": "dra",
      "bookSlug": "proverbs",
      "chapterNumber": 20,
      "verseNumber": 11,
      "referenceLabel": "Proverbs 20:11",
      "text": "By his inclinations a child is known, if his works be clean and right.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "dra:proverbs.20.12",
      "translationId": "dra",
      "bookSlug": "proverbs",
      "chapterNumber": 20,
      "verseNumber": 12,
      "referenceLabel": "Proverbs 20:12",
      "text": "The hearing ear, and the seeing eye, the Lord hath made them both.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "dra:proverbs.20.13",
      "translationId": "dra",
      "bookSlug": "proverbs",
      "chapterNumber": 20,
      "verseNumber": 13,
      "referenceLabel": "Proverbs 20:13",
      "text": "Love not sleep, lest poverty oppress thee: open thy eyes, and be filled with bread.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "dra:proverbs.20.14",
      "translationId": "dra",
      "bookSlug": "proverbs",
      "chapterNumber": 20,
      "verseNumber": 14,
      "referenceLabel": "Proverbs 20:14",
      "text": "It is naught, it is naught, saith every buyer: and when he is gone away, then he will boast.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "dra:proverbs.20.15",
      "translationId": "dra",
      "bookSlug": "proverbs",
      "chapterNumber": 20,
      "verseNumber": 15,
      "referenceLabel": "Proverbs 20:15",
      "text": "There is gold and a multitude of jewels: but the lips of knowledge are a precious vessel.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "dra:proverbs.20.16",
      "translationId": "dra",
      "bookSlug": "proverbs",
      "chapterNumber": 20,
      "verseNumber": 16,
      "referenceLabel": "Proverbs 20:16",
      "text": "Take away the garment of him that is surety for a stranger, and take a pledge from him for strangers.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "dra:proverbs.20.17",
      "translationId": "dra",
      "bookSlug": "proverbs",
      "chapterNumber": 20,
      "verseNumber": 17,
      "referenceLabel": "Proverbs 20:17",
      "text": "The bread of lying is sweet to a man: but afterwards his mouth shall be filled with gravel.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "dra:proverbs.20.18",
      "translationId": "dra",
      "bookSlug": "proverbs",
      "chapterNumber": 20,
      "verseNumber": 18,
      "referenceLabel": "Proverbs 20:18",
      "text": "Designs are strengthened by counsels: and wars are to be managed by governments.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "dra:proverbs.20.19",
      "translationId": "dra",
      "bookSlug": "proverbs",
      "chapterNumber": 20,
      "verseNumber": 19,
      "referenceLabel": "Proverbs 20:19",
      "text": "Meddle not with him that revealeth secrets, and walketh deceitfully, and openeth wide his lips.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "dra:proverbs.20.20",
      "translationId": "dra",
      "bookSlug": "proverbs",
      "chapterNumber": 20,
      "verseNumber": 20,
      "referenceLabel": "Proverbs 20:20",
      "text": "He that curseth his father, and mother, his lamp shall be put out in the midst of darkness.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "dra:proverbs.20.21",
      "translationId": "dra",
      "bookSlug": "proverbs",
      "chapterNumber": 20,
      "verseNumber": 21,
      "referenceLabel": "Proverbs 20:21",
      "text": "The inheritance gotten hastily in the beginning, in the end shall be without a blessing.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "dra:proverbs.20.22",
      "translationId": "dra",
      "bookSlug": "proverbs",
      "chapterNumber": 20,
      "verseNumber": 22,
      "referenceLabel": "Proverbs 20:22",
      "text": "Say not: I will return evil: wait for the Lord, and he will deliver thee.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "dra:proverbs.20.23",
      "translationId": "dra",
      "bookSlug": "proverbs",
      "chapterNumber": 20,
      "verseNumber": 23,
      "referenceLabel": "Proverbs 20:23",
      "text": "Diverse weights are an abomination before the Lord: a deceitful balance is not good.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "dra:proverbs.20.24",
      "translationId": "dra",
      "bookSlug": "proverbs",
      "chapterNumber": 20,
      "verseNumber": 24,
      "referenceLabel": "Proverbs 20:24",
      "text": "The steps of men are guided by the Lord: but who is the man that can understand his own way?",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "dra:proverbs.20.25",
      "translationId": "dra",
      "bookSlug": "proverbs",
      "chapterNumber": 20,
      "verseNumber": 25,
      "referenceLabel": "Proverbs 20:25",
      "text": "It is ruin to a man to devour holy ones, and after vows to retract.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "dra:proverbs.20.26",
      "translationId": "dra",
      "bookSlug": "proverbs",
      "chapterNumber": 20,
      "verseNumber": 26,
      "referenceLabel": "Proverbs 20:26",
      "text": "A wise king scattereth the wicked, and bringeth over them the wheel.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "dra:proverbs.20.27",
      "translationId": "dra",
      "bookSlug": "proverbs",
      "chapterNumber": 20,
      "verseNumber": 27,
      "referenceLabel": "Proverbs 20:27",
      "text": "The spirit of a man is the lamp of the Lord, which searcheth all the hidden things of the bowels.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "dra:proverbs.20.28",
      "translationId": "dra",
      "bookSlug": "proverbs",
      "chapterNumber": 20,
      "verseNumber": 28,
      "referenceLabel": "Proverbs 20:28",
      "text": "Mercy and truth preserve the king, and his throne is strengthened by clemency.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "dra:proverbs.20.29",
      "translationId": "dra",
      "bookSlug": "proverbs",
      "chapterNumber": 20,
      "verseNumber": 29,
      "referenceLabel": "Proverbs 20:29",
      "text": "The joy of young men is their strength: and the dignity of old men, their grey hairs.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "dra:proverbs.20.30",
      "translationId": "dra",
      "bookSlug": "proverbs",
      "chapterNumber": 20,
      "verseNumber": 30,
      "referenceLabel": "Proverbs 20:30",
      "text": "The blueness of a wound shall wipe away evils: and stripes in the more inward parts of the belly.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    }
  ]
}
